{"lemma":"أَبْجَدَيْ","slug":"أَبْجَدَيْ","root":"#.ب.ج.د","root_slug":"_-ب-ج-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-ج-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alphabet, abjad"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ABC, nuts and bolts (elementary facts, simple truths)","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the first four letters of the Arabic alphabet arranged in the old style, which is similar to the Greek and Hebrew order: أ ب ج د. Compare Classical Syriac ܐܒܓܕ."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8","headword_ar":"اَبْجَدْ","root":"Abjd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first of a series of eight words comprising the letters of the Arabic alphabet"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the order in which they were originally disposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeing with that of the Hebrew and Aramaic, but with six additional letters: they are variously written and pronounced; generally as follows:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abojada haw~azo HuT~iY kalamano saEofaSo qara$ato vaxa*o DaZago","text_ar":"اَبْجَدَ هَوَّزْ حُطِّى كَلَمَنْ سَعْفَصْ قَرَشَتْ ثَخَذْ ضَظَغْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the Arabs of Western Africa write the latter four thus:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SEfD qrst vx* Zg$","text_ar":"صعفض قرست ثخذ ظغش"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bjd","text_ar":"بجد"},{"kind":"text","text":": [in both of which are related several fables concerning the origin of these words:]) accord. to the general opinion, the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abjd","text_ar":"ابجد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of foreign origin, [like each of the words following it,] and therefore its first letter [as well as each of the others] is a radical. (TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abojadu","text_ar":"الاَبْجَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The alphabet."},{"kind":"text","text":"You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huruwfu","text_ar":"حُرُوفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abojadi","text_ar":"الاَبْجَدِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The letters of the alphabet."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  It is probable (as De Sacy has observed in his Ar. Gram., 2nd ed., i. 8,) that the Arabic alphabet originally consisted of only twenty-two letters: for some of the ancient Arabs called Saturday"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abjd","text_ar":"ابجد"},{"kind":"text","text":", Sunday"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hwz~","text_ar":"هوزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so on to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qr$t","text_ar":"قرشت"},{"kind":"text","text":"inclusive; calling Friday"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earuwbapu","text_ar":"عَرُوبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  In the lexicon entitled “El-'Eyn,” the letters of the alphabet are arranged nearly according to their places of utterance; as follows:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x","text_ar":"خ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"g","text_ar":"غ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": and this order has been followed in the Tahdheeb and Mohkam and some other lexicons.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}